text: Petropavlovka () is a rural locality (a selo) in Baranovsky Selsoviet, Narimanovsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 375 as of 2010. There are 10 streets. == Geography == It is located 10 km NNW from Narimanov. == References == Category:Rural localities in Narimanovsky District
title: Petropavlovka, Astrakhan Oblast
